										<div class="accordion-content">
											<p>You have three months after first setting up your device to take advantage of your free year of Apple&nbsp;TV+.</p>
										</div>
									</div>
								</li>
								<li id="where-can-I-watch-apple-tv+" class="accordion-item" data-accordion-item>
									<div class="header-wrapper">
										<h3 class="accordion-headline typography-eyebrow">Where can I watch Apple&nbsp;TV+?</h3>
										<button class="icon icon-plus" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="accordion-panel-5" aria-labelledby="accordion-label-5">
									</button>
									</div>
									<div class="accordion-panel" id="accordion-panel-5" aria-hidden="true">
										<div class="accordion-content">
											<p>You can watch Apple&nbsp;TV+ shows and movies on the Apple&nbsp;TV app and <a href="https://tv.apple.com/">tv.apple.com</a>. The Apple&nbsp;TV app is already on Apple devices. But if you’ve removed it, you can download it again from the <a href="https://apps.apple.com/app/apple-tv/id1174078549">App Store</a>. You can also watch Apple TV+ on Samsung and LG smart TVs, as well as Roku and Amazon Fire TV devices, if they support the Apple TV app.</p>
										</div>
									</div>
								</li>
								<li id="what-is-apple-tv+-app" class="accordion-item" data-accordion-item>
